GoAir Hires Air One’s De Roni as CEO to Oversee India Expansion

-- B y   K a r t h i k e y a n   S u n d a r a m
-- 
2011-06-16T13:34:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/goair-hires-air-one-s-de-roni-as-ceo-to-oversee-india-expansion.html
GoAirlines ( India ) Ltd., a low-fare
airline, named Giorgio De Roni, the former chief revenue officer
at Italian carrier Air One, as chief executive officer.  De Roni will oversee expansion of operations, GoAir
Managing Director Jeh Wadia said in Mumbai today, adding the
Indian carrier has agreed to buy 72 Airbus SAS A320neo aircraft.
 SpiceJet Ltd. (SJET) , the only listed Indian discount carrier, in
October also had named an expatriate Neil Raymond Mills as chief
executive officer.  Jet Airways, the nation’s biggest airline by market value,
had in May 2010 named Nikos Kardassis, its head of American
operations, as chief executive officer to succeed Wolfgang
Prock-Schauer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karthikeyan Sundaram in  New Delhi  at 
